          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sept. 849</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>134 Elm St.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>מיסטער ליססער</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <persName role="author">G. Middleman</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>134 Elm St.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>Septr 20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5610</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Dear Sir/</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I would have <sic>replyd</sic> to<lb/> your
                                        request immediately upon knowing you had written but
                                                  <persName>Mr DeYoung</persName><lb/> only placed
                                        your Letter in my possession<lb/> yesterday—altho he
                                        mentioned to one some<lb/> long time since that you had made
                                        some<lb/> request for a Book or something (he could not
                                        remember) of me.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>which he would inform me of<del>f</del><lb/> In respect to the
                                        Letter, you wish<lb/> of me <persName>Mr
                                                  Middleman's</persName> Letter will<lb/> explain—I
                                        have some other matter<lb/> to communicate to you which I
                                        will<lb/> attend to immediately after <add>יידיש</add><lb/>
                                        in the mean time receive my<lb/> best wishes for your
                                        happiness<lb/> and believe me to be yours<lb/>
                                                  sincerely—<persName role="author">Ansel
                                                  Leo</persName></p>
                              <p>If you wish to publish <persName>Mr<lb/> Middleman's</persName>
                                        Letter I must request<lb/> you will do so without extracting<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">one word</hi> from the original<lb/>
                                        otherwise neither he nor I wish<lb/> to see it in print</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">Yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">
                                        <persName role="author">
                                                  <hi rend="underline">AL</hi>
                                        </persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">private</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>371—Walnut St</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>רב מווארשא ובית דודו בלודג</add>
                                        <placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                                        <date>Sept 20, 1849</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <placeName>134 Elm St.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(11)"><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. Leo</persName> has indeed shown me
                                        your<lb/> letter, asking that he send you the letter of<lb/>
                                        the Rabbi of <placeName>Warsaw</placeName>, and
                                                  <del>from</del> the Bette Din<lb/> with regard to
                                        the law of the *<hi rend="underline">Get</hi> which was sent
                                        by<lb/> post. This letter was sent by the Rabbi<lb/> and the
                                        court of <placeName>Warsaw</placeName> to the
                                        undersigned<lb/> at the address of <persName>Rev. Mr.
                                                  Leo.</persName> I was the one<lb/> who arranged
                                        this <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> and sent it by post<lb/>
                                        to <placeName>Warsaw</placeName>, but God forbid that I
                                        should<lb/> be the cause for the stumbling of many by<lb/>
                                        having this letter translated into English<lb/> and
                                        published in the “Occident,” so that every<lb/> wicked and
                                                  <add>?</add>fulous man who never<lb/> studied and
                                        doesn't know what to do<lb/> with a <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >Get</hi> of this sort, nor even with an<lb/>
                                        ordinary <hi rend="underline">Get</hi>, hearing that a <hi
                                                  rend="underline">Get</hi> of this<lb/> kind was
                                        written will pride himself by<lb/> paying. “I, too, can do
                                        so,” and he<lb/> will send a <hi rend="underline">Get</hi>
                                        from a husband to his wife.<lb/> The fact is that legally
                                        this woman<lb/> who asked for a divorce is still</p>
                              <p>*Bill of Divorce</p>
                              <pb n="5"/>
                              <p>married and has never been divorced,<lb/> because the one who
                                        arranged the<lb/> divorce, knows nothing about the law<lb/>
                                        governing such cases. That is why I<lb/> refrain from
                                        sending you this letter to<lb/> publish in the “Occident”,
                                        for I have no<lb/> desire that evil should come through
                                        you<lb/> and a stumbling block for
                                                  <placeName>Israel</placeName>, so<lb/> that
                                        through me <del>illegitimate<add>?</add></del><lb/>
                                        illegitimacy should increase <del>through<lb/> me</del>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Your friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <persName role="author">Godol Middleman</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
